msgstr "They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:20.4"
msgid "‘Saṃvibhajati puññāni karotī’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "They share it and make merit. This is the third ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:20.5"
msgid "‘Te ca bhoge gathito mucchito ajjhosanno anādīnavadassāvī anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjatī’ti, iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho. "
msgstr "They enjoy that wealth tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape. This is the one ground for criticism. "

msgctxt "an10.91:20.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi tīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho. (9) "
msgstr "This pleasure seeker may be praised on these three grounds, and criticized on this one. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an10.91:21.1"
msgid "Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī catūhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit. And they enjoy that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. They may be praised on four grounds. "

msgctxt "an10.91:21.2"
msgid "‘Dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "They seek for wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means. This is the first ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:21.3"
msgid "‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:21.4"
msgid "‘Saṃvibhajati puññāni karotī’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "They share it and make merit. This is the third ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:21.5"
msgid "‘Te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjatī’ti, iminā catutthena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "They enjoy that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. This is the fourth ground for praise. "

msgctxt "an10.91:21.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi catūhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso. (10) "
msgstr "This pleasure seeker may be praised on these four grounds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.182, sc22
msgctxt "an10.91:22.1"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapati, dasa kāmabhogī santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These are the ten pleasure seekers found in the world. "

#. VAR: pāmokkho → mokkho (si)
msgctxt "an10.91:22.2"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca. "
msgstr "The pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit, and who uses that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the ten. "

msgctxt "an10.91:22.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo. Sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati. "
msgstr "From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
#. VAR: pāmokkho → mokkho (si)
msgctxt "an10.91:23.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, gahapati, imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit, and who uses that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the ten.” "

